The paper deals with image deblurring, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The use of graphs and graph-based methods is a popular approach in these fields, which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of graph spectral filtering and graph total variation, which are techniques commonly used in graph signal processing and graph theory, suggesting that the paper may also belong to the cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories. The paper also discusses optimization techniques and regularization methods, which are common in the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a specific algorithm for Gaussian deblurring, which suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
